---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
const updated = '2026-06-19'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — book·lore"
  description="What book·lore collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
>
  <section class="spine page">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">book·lore</a> / <a href="/legal/">colophon</a> / privacy</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Who runs this</h2>
      <p>
        lore.oriz.in is operated by Chirag Singhal, based in Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India.
        Contact: <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>. It is part of
        the <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz</a> family of free static sites.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and country.
          Cookieless. No personal identifiers.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reading state</strong> — the bottle-green ribbon on each book page writes
          your last-read paragraph to <code>localStorage</code> (key
          <code>bookLore:&lt;slug&gt;:para</code>). This stays on your device.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms which forwards
          to my email.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        book·lore is fully public. There is no sign-in, no account, and no server-side
        store of anything you do here.
      </p>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
        <li>No accounts, no passwords, no personal profiles.</li>
        <li>No selling of personal data.</li>
        <li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe (and right now there is no signup).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Reading state lives only in your browser — clear your site data to wipe it. Under
        India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct, and delete any personal
        data we hold — contact the <a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        book·lore is not directed at children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new date at the top.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
